entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: hi i am ellie thanks for coming in today i was created to talk to people in a safe and secure environment i am not a therapist but i am here to learn about people and would love to learn about you i will ask a few questions to get us started and please feel free to tell me anything your answers are totally confidential are you okay with this

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay so how are you doing today

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: fine just tired

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry to hear that where are you from originally

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: california

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: really

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: from hollywood

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am good i do not really have a temper

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was my ex husband about money

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: people lying cheating conniving drug addicts you know just ugly people people that are hideous in the inside you know

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah yeah who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: jesus christ that is about it my mother when she was alive well she still is a positive influence but nobody really but jesus

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay what is one of your most memorable experiences

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: memorable experiences i do not know i can not really think of one right now

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.text: have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was nineteen eighty four

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is a long time

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i could not deal with it so i had to see a psychiatrist

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what were your symptoms

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: horrified could not sleep panicked major anxiety yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay did you think you had a problem before you found out

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes i do

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it could be if you see the right doctor if you see if yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how has seeing a therapist affected you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it gives you the opportunity to talk to somebody and hopefully they can give you answers most of em do not they try to find the answers inside of you and get it out of you but it is just good to be able to talk to somebody that is kinda biased neutral

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: really depressed extremely depressed

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: poverty yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see i see

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah i am a lot more tired i sleep longer and i i just do not have the drive motivation that i did before

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: just try to be strong just have to get through it you know

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: there are always trade offs in life are not there

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes there are

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what would you say are some of your best qualities

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am a well i would say a perfectionist but that is not really a good quality cause it can get dangerous i am just artistic i am good at a lot of things i am really good at a lot of things but xxx

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you give me an example of that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i am good at i am a good hairdresser and makeup artist i crochet and knit really well make jewelry not good with computers or phones though electronics

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah i keep a perfect house or well when i am not depressed like this i was a perfect wife the perfect wife

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: so yeah but not anymore cause i am divorced now but it was not me it was him so

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: he was on drugs so he chose eh the drugs were were too much problems

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things that usually put you in a good mood

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well if i can have my starbucks and my orange gina i drink orange gina everyday and i smoke cigarettes unfortunately but it is always good to have those because you know i am addicted to them and then if i can eat something really good and healthy at nighttime and in fact i well basically if i have something to do if i have a goal somewhere to go something to do like today even puts me in a good mood

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah otherwise i would be afraid that i would stay home and just lay in bed or farm all day i could farm for eight hours on farmville

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay i think i have asked everything i need to thanks for sharing your thoughts with me

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: you are welcome nice to meet you
